#compdef cloudsmith-kubernetes-credential-provider
# ============================================================================
# cloudsmith-kubernetes-credential-provider - Cloudsmith
#   credential provider plugin for kubelet image pulls
#   (Go, Cloudsmith)
#
# Author : Cloudsmith
# Upstream: https://github.com/cloudsmith-io/
#          cloudsmith-kubernetes-credential-provider
# go module: github.com/cloudsmith-io/
#            cloudsmith-kubernetes-credential-provider
#
# This binary implements the Kubelet Credential Provider
# interface (KEP-4412: projected service account tokens
# for kubelet image credential providers). It runs as an
# out-of-tree plugin invoked by kubelet just before an
# image pull from a Cloudsmith registry. The plugin
# receives a `CredentialProviderRequest` JSON document on
# stdin (containing the image being pulled + the projected
# service account OIDC token), exchanges the SA token with
# Cloudsmith's auth service for a registry-scoped Docker
# registry credential, and writes a
# `CredentialProviderResponse` to stdout that kubelet then
# uses for the registry HTTP basic-auth handshake.
#
# Usage:
#   cloudsmith-kubernetes-credential-provider [--config <file>]
#   cloudsmith-kubernetes-credential-provider version
#
# Flags (cobra + Kubernetes klog standard layout):
#   --config <file>       - path to YAML configuration
#                           file (registry patterns,
#                           Cloudsmith service slug,
#                           retry backoff settings,
#                           HTTP timeout / idle conn
#                           tuning, log level, optional
#                           insecure-skip-verify flag,
#                           custom HTTP headers)
#   -h, --help            - print help
#   -v, --version         - print version, commit, build
#                           date
#
# Subcommands:
#   version               - print verbose version info
#                           (delegates to klog with cfg
#                           log level applied)
#
# Operationally invoked by kubelet, not by humans - but
# direct invocation works for debugging:
#   echo '{"apiVersion":"...","image":"docker.cloudsmith.io/...","serviceAccountToken":"..."}' \
#     | cloudsmith-kubernetes-credential-provider --config /etc/kubelet/cloudsmith.yaml
#
# The golang-jwt lane is built on `github.com/golang-jwt/
# jwt/v5 v5.2.2` (declared verbatim at upstream go.mod
# HEAD as a direct dep, imported from main.go), the
# canonical Go JWT library by the golang-jwt working group
# - github.com/golang-jwt/jwt, 8000+ stars. The library is
# the community-maintained fork of dgrijalva/jwt-go after
# the original author abandoned the project in 2020; the
# import path was intentionally moved to `github.com/
# golang-jwt/jwt` (no `dgrijalva` prefix) to signal the
# governance change while keeping the API surface mostly
# backward-compatible.
#
# v5 is the current major and is a partial rewrite that
# tightened the parser + validator (stricter algorithm
# enforcement, claims interface change, more explicit
# error types). Compliant with RFC 7519 (JWT), RFC 7515
# (JWS), and RFC 7518 (JWA). Supports HS256/HS384/HS512,
# RS256/RS384/RS512, PS256/PS384/PS512, ES256/ES384/ES512,
# and EdDSA.
#
# cloudsmith-kubernetes-credential-provider uses
# golang-jwt to parse the projected SA token kubelet
# hands it before forwarding to Cloudsmith - the plugin
# extracts the SA's audience claim to determine which
# Cloudsmith service slug to authenticate against, and
# checks the `exp` claim to refuse expired tokens before
# even contacting Cloudsmith.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 241 :: JSON Web Tokens (RFC 7519 sign + verify)
# Round 1422 :: Go slot 2 of 4 :: continues Axis 241
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : Keats/jsonwebtoken           [R1421 _pushpin-handler]
#   Go      : golang-jwt/jwt               [R1422 THIS FILE]
#   TS/Node : auth0/node-jsonwebtoken      [R1423 closing]
#
# golang-jwt/jwt is structurally interesting in this axis
# because it has the most colorful governance history of
# the three lanes. The library started as dgrijalva/jwt-go
# (Dave Grijalva), reached canonical status across the Go
# ecosystem by ~2019, then went unmaintained in early
# 2020. A community fork emerged at golang-jwt/jwt later
# in 2020 + 2021 with the explicit goal of preserving the
# import path semantics - existing code calling
# `github.com/dgrijalva/jwt-go.NewWithClaims` could
# upgrade to `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt.NewWithClaims`
# without API breakage. The v5 release in 2023 broke that
# vow intentionally - the project decided that 4 years of
# back-compat cruft was hampering security hardening, and
# shipped a tightened API + parser. The transition is
# now mostly complete; v4 remains supported on a slow
# security-only schedule.
#
# Structural commentary on the Cosmos of jwt impls:
#   - Rust (Keats/jsonwebtoken): single-author maintained
#     since 2017; crypto backend is `ring` by default with
#     `rust_crypto` opt-in feature
#   - Go (golang-jwt/jwt): community-fork of dgrijalva/
#     jwt-go after the 2020 takeover; crypto via stdlib
#     crypto/* packages
#   - Node (auth0/node-jsonwebtoken): Auth0-corporately-
#     maintained since 2014; crypto via Node's stdlib
#     crypto module
#
# Cross-language interop happens at the wire format level
# (Base64URL(header).Base64URL(payload).Base64URL(sig)).
# A JWT signed with HS256 + the same secret verifies
# identically across all three lanes. RS256 / ES256 keys
# are typically distributed as PEM-encoded PKCS#8 or
# SubjectPublicKeyInfo, so loading the same key into any
# lane gives byte-identical verification semantics.
# ============================================================================

_cloudsmith-kubernetes-credential-provider() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args
    local curcontext="$curcontext" ret=1

    _arguments -C \
        '--config[path to YAML configuration file]:file:_files -g "*.{yaml,yml,json}"' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]' \
        '(- *)'{-v,--version}'[print version, commit, build date]' \
        '1: :_cloudsmith_ckcp_cmds' \
        '*::arg:->args' \
    && ret=0

    case $state in
        args)
            case $words[1] in
                version)
                    _arguments \
                        '--config[path to YAML configuration file]:file:_files -g "*.{yaml,yml,json}"' \
                        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]'
                    ;;
            esac
            ;;
    esac

    return ret
}

_cloudsmith_ckcp_cmds() {
    local -a cmds
    cmds=(
        'version:print version, commit, build date (verbose)'
    )
    _describe -t commands 'cloudsmith-kubernetes-credential-provider command' cmds
}

_cloudsmith-kubernetes-credential-provider "$@"
